.TH HSH 1 "April 2026" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.br
.B echo
.I "command"
|
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command-line interpreter that reads commands from standard input or from a file and executes them.

.SH USAGE

.SS Interactive Mode
In interactive mode,
.B hsh
displays a prompt ("$ ") and waits for the user to type a command. After executing the command, the prompt is displayed again.

.SS Non-Interactive Mode
In non-interactive mode,
.B hsh
reads commands from standard input (via pipe or redirection), executes them, and exits when all commands are processed.

.SH COMMAND EXECUTION

.B hsh
executes commands in the following order:

.IP 1. 4
Checks if the command is a built-in (exit, env)
.IP 2. 4
If not a built-in, searches for the command:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
If the command contains '/' (absolute or relative path), uses it directly
.IP \(bu 2
Otherwise, searches for the command in directories listed in the PATH environment variable
.RE
.IP 3. 4
If found, executes the command in a child process using fork() and execve()
.IP 4. 4
Waits for the command to complete before returning to the prompt

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS

.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell.
.TP
.B env
Prints all environment variables.

.SH RETURN VALUE
.B hsh
returns the exit status of the last executed command.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PATH
List of directories to search for executable commands, separated by colons (:).

.SH EXAMPLES

.SS Interactive Mode
.nf
$ ./hsh
$ ls -l
total 100
-rw-r--r-- 1 user user 1234 Apr 19 10:00 main.c
$ pwd
/home/user/simple_shell
$ exit
.fi

.SS Non-Interactive Mode
.nf
$ echo "ls" | ./hsh
main.c shell.c hsh

$ echo -e "pwd\\nls\\nexit" | ./hsh
/home/user/simple_shell
main.c shell.c hsh
.fi

.SH ERROR MESSAGES
When a command is not found,
.B hsh
prints an error message to stderr in the format:
.PP
.I ./hsh: 1: command: not found
.PP
Where
.I ./hsh
is the name of the shell (from argv[0]),
.I 1
is the line number, and
.I command
is the name of the command that was not found.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.B hsh
returns 0 on success and 1 on error.

.SH FILES
None.

.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.PP
The following features are not implemented:
.IP \(bu 2
Command separators (;, &&, ||)
.IP \(bu 2
Pipes (|)
.IP \(bu 2
Redirections (>, <, >>)
.IP \(bu 2
Wildcards (*, ?)
.IP \(bu 2
Variable expansion ($VAR)
.IP \(bu 2
Quotes handling
.IP \(bu 2
Comments (#)

